6:
How DARE you speak of peace! 
After all we've been through!
8: Cowardly witch! Get out of our sight!
15:
Hey, we any closer to that
something-something sage you
keep raving about?
19:
I told you, man, it's Nevia Tabbinth,
the Sharp-Eyed Sage. And we
should be there shortly.
22:
You said she retired years ago,
right? Why're you trying to get her
on your side anyway? She doesn't
sound like she'd be much help to
your cause.
25:
Oh yeah? Even if I tell you she was
calling for peace waaay before any
of us did?
28:
Evidently she foretold the fall of the
catfolk if the war continued. Pretty
scary, right? If it's true, that is.
30:
But we could really use someone
who can see the future right about
now. That's why we're here.
37:
You could say that. But that's just all
the more reason to get her on our
side!
40: Now come on, let's recruit us a sage!
43:
We appreciate your patience. Lady
Nevia is now—
47:
It is good to see you, Claw, the
herald of peace... and Nimbus, son
of Whitetail.
49:
It is also a pleasure to finally meet
our visitors from another world.
53:
Did you see all that in your visions of
the future?
56:
My clairvoyance offers but a
glimpse of what is to come... The
rest must be discerned from what
clues fate brings us.
60:
So in other words... Our being here
lines up with your vision, right?
63:
Hehe... That is correct. Although I will
admit I am making assumptions.
67:
Ah, my apologies! After I glimpse
into the future, I tend to forget small
courtesies such as introductions...
71:
Then... does that mean you know
why we're here as well?
74:
Indeed I do. I hope to be of great
assistance to your cause.
78:
Well, at least we don't have to waste
time explaining ourselves! And
welcome aboard! We're happy to
have you.
82:
It is a shame that I must put a
damper on that happiness.
85:
I do not foresee this peace we
experience now lasting long.
88:
The stars and crystals foretell the
end, and what I saw, heard, and
smelled in my own visions did
nothing to ease my fears.
90:
I am sure you understand this as
well. That is what brought you here,
no?
94:
Halt! Claudius Navelle, you shall pay
for your crimes with your life!
98: Why... Why don't any of you listen?
102:
Why can't we just talk to one
another?! Taking me down won't
change anything!
105:
But it will. Both the catfolk and
dogfolk are ready to bare their
fangs!
106:
But in the end, WE will stand
triumphant!
109:
I knew this was coming, but I've
heard quite enough!
113: Oh, how I pity you all...
117:
I hear movement outside. It seems
we are surrounded.
129:
Whoa, wait, what are you thinking?
We're sitting ducks here!
133: No, this is the perfect spot.
136:
Well, what do we have here? Trying
to make it easier to capture you all?
139:
Not at all. I simply thought cleanup
would be easiest here.
142:
Winds of Ancients, Bearers of the
Seeds of Life! Extend thine arms and
embrace those filled with hate!
145:
Ngh! Curse you and your wretched
powers, witch!
148:
Unfortunately, I cannot claim this
power as my own. I knew this day
would come, so I have merely been
placing enchantments on the trees
for years in preparation.
152:
Whoa... If I didn't believe in your
visions before, I definitely do now...
153:
Are you... sure there is nothing we
can do to change the future you
saw?
160:
Peace may have reduced the
amount of bloodshed, but it also
sheds light on the crookedness that
was previously obscured by war.
163:
Poverty, disparity among the
classes... Others will seek to place
blame for these somewhere. As for
the target of that brewing hatred...
167:
Surely it would fall to the
bloodstained soldiers.
171:
But that's wrong! If anybody is to
blame, it's us—the government.
174:
I want to change our world for the
better. That's why I need your help.
178:
Why do you persist? The catfolk and
dogfolk will seek a villain to blame.
Just as they have done in the past.
181:
That weakness guides the stream of
fate in this world. Even with my
predictions, we will create but a
ripple in those waters.
190:
Hehe... You're still gonna help out,
aren't you? You said you would.
195:
Indeed, I will do all I can to help. Even
if this path ultimately leads to
destruction.
198:
Alright, then I think you should go to
Starview Village first!
202:
By all means. You are welcome to
join us.
211:
Hehe, and what would you have me
do in this otherworldly town?
216:
I can't really say for sure what will
happen, but I just want you to work
with everyone there—especially Alk!
226:
Haha, yeah, a regular dose of Alk
could be just what you need.
231:
Huh? Wait, what do you mean by
that?
236: Sorry, Alk, but just play along, okay?
239: I know you can do it!
243:
I look forward to our adventures
together, Alk.
